&lt;h2 id="installation-and-environment-creation">Installation and Environment Creation
&lt;/h2>&lt;p>Official installation reference:
&lt;a class="link" href="https://docs.conda.io/projects/conda/en/stable/user-guide/install/index.html"
target="_blank" rel="noopener"
>
Installing conda - conda documentation
&lt;/a>
&lt;/p>
&lt;p>Download link:
&lt;a class="link" href="https://www.anaconda.com/download/success?reg=skipped"
target="_blank" rel="noopener"
>
Download anaconda
&lt;/a>
&lt;/p>
&lt;p>You can download Miniconda and set up environments manually as needed.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>Create a running environment:&lt;/p>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;div class="chroma">
&lt;table class="lntable">&lt;tr>&lt;td class="lntd">
&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma">&lt;code>&lt;span class="lnt">1
&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/td>
&lt;td class="lntd">
&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma">&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash">&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">conda create -n env_name &lt;span class="nv">python&lt;/span>&lt;span class="o">=&lt;/span>3.13 -y
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/td>&lt;/tr>&lt;/table>
&lt;/div>
&lt;/div>&lt;p>Activate the environment:&lt;/p>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;div class="chroma">
&lt;table class="lntable">&lt;tr>&lt;td class="lntd">
&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma">&lt;code>&lt;span class="lnt">1
&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/td>
&lt;td class="lntd">
&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma">&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash">&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">conda activate env_name
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/td>&lt;/tr>&lt;/table>
&lt;/div>
&lt;/div>&lt;h2 id="installing-pytorch">Installing PyTorch
&lt;/h2>&lt;p>For the CPU version, use this command directly:&lt;/p>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;div class="chroma">
&lt;table class="lntable">&lt;tr>&lt;td class="lntd">
&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma">&lt;code>&lt;span class="lnt">1
&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/td>
&lt;td class="lntd">
&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma">&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash">&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">pip install torch torchvision torchaudio
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/td>&lt;/tr>&lt;/table>
&lt;/div>
&lt;/div>&lt;p>For the GPU version, visit the official site at
&lt;a class="link" href="https://pytorch.org/get-started/locally/"
target="_blank" rel="noopener"
>
https://pytorch.org/get-started/locally/
&lt;/a>
to get the installation command.&lt;/p></description></item></channel></rss>